  login page and a table to view and download responses.
overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a Sleep Questionnaire
  Application by integrating a database for response storage, a
  client-accessible admin dashboard, and an authentication system. After
  evaluating the existing codebase, the assistant identified the need for a new
  database schema for questionnaire responses, API endpoints for data capture
  and retrieval (including CSV export), and a secure admin interface. Key
  decisions included using NeonDB with Prisma for the database, implementing a
  straightforward password-based authentication system, and combining
  demographic data fields as per the SOW and existing form. The implementation
  involved updating data models, creating new API routes, developing
  authentication helpers, and building the admin dashboard with login and data
  display functionalities, ensuring all questionnaire submissions are now stored
  and accessible.
